Beef Stroganoff

2 lbs, chuck roast in half-inch slices
4 tbsp, butter
1, onion
1 tsp, salt
1 tsp, pepper
1 cup, mushroom, sliced
2 cloves, garlic, minced
1.25 cups, beef broth
1/2 cup, sour cream
2 cups, rice or pasta

Serves 4-6, 40 minutes

Preheat Instant Pot on SAUTÉ. Melt the butter.

Add the onion and sauté 3 minutes.

Season the meat strips with salt and pepper. Add to the pot.

Cook, stirring occasionally, for 2 minutes until starting to brown.

Add the mushrooms and cook for 2 more minutes.

Add the garlic and sauté for 1 minute.

Press CANCEL button to stop SAUTE function.

Pour broth and stir well. Close and lock lid.

Select MANUAL and cook at HIGH pressure for 15 min.

When time goes off use Quick Release. Add the sour cream and mix well. Close and let sit 5 minutes.

Serve on rice or egg noodles.
